  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators hypothesize that a risk score composed of age, sex, and the components of
      commonly ordered laboratory panels will be predictive of mortality in trauma patients, and
      will help improve clinicians' ability to make more accurate mortality predictions at the time
      of admission.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
